Import the package and utilities

{% raw %} 
from pathlib import Path
from fastcore.utils import *
from ddg_images_downloader.images import *
{% endraw %}

Create the destination directory

{% raw %} 
!mkdir -p /content/data/fruits
{% endraw %}

Define the search terms, search pattern and directory

{% raw %} 
fruit_types = ['apple','banana','orange']
search_pattern = '{0} fruit'
path = Path('/content/data/fruits'); Path.BASE_PATH = path
{% endraw %}

Download the image urls into text file (each term in a separate file)

{% raw %} 
download_search_urls(path, fruit_types, search_pattern, scroll_count=5, sleep=5)

apple fruit 499
banana fruit 517
orange fruit 501
{% endraw %}

The text files should have been created.

{% raw %} 
path.ls()

(#3) [Path('banana.txt'),Path('apple.txt'),Path('orange.txt')]
{% endraw %}

Download the images based on the urls listed in each text file, placing them in separate directories (one for each search term)
